* Linux

0. Prerequisite 
   - asdf (by invoke (require :asdf))
   - gcc
   - Intel MKL

1. $ cd src/

2. $ make

It will show something like below
gcc -shared -fPIC -fomit-frame-pointer -march=core2 -pipe -msse -msse2 -msse3 -msse4.1 -Wall -o lapack_wrapper.so \
		-L/opt/intel/mkl/10.1.2.024/lib/em64t -lmkl_gf_lp64 \
		-lmkl_gnu_thread -lmkl_core -lm -lgomp -lgfortran -lpthread \
		lapack_wrapper.c
                
3. (asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op :lapack).

You need to make asdf aware about the .asd files. e.g. Have the
   blas.asd and lapack.asd symlinked to your current directory

